description: This file implements a part of a STUN (Session Traversal Utilities for NAT) client, specifically the 'Simple Client Object' interface functions including query, process, and notification handlers for incoming packets and socket events. It contains function implementations like StunScoScuowoBQuery, StunScoScuowoBProcess, and StunScoScuowoBNotify.

methods.name: ULONG StunScoScuowoBQuery(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,PVOID buffer,ULONG ulSize)
methods.description: Determines processing mode for an incoming packet based on the client's active state.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS StunScoScuowoBProcess(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,PVOID buffer,ULONG ulSize)
methods.description: Processes incoming STUN packets, delegating to specific response handlers based on the message type.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS StunScoScuowoBNotify(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,ULONG ulEvent,ANSC_HANDLE hReserved)
methods.description: Handles socket-related events, currently a stub that always returns success.
